{"format": "tiptap/v1", "updatedAt": "2026-06-23T09:21:39.833Z", "doc": {"type": "doc", "content": [{"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "image", "attrs": {"src": "data:image/svg+xml;base64,", "alt": "os & pathlib — concept overview"}}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "What they are"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}, {"type": "code"}], "text": "os"}, {"type": "text", "text": " is Python's low-level interface to the underlying operating system. It gives access to environment variables, process information, file system operations (create/delete/rename files and directories), and path manipulation through its sub-module "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "os.path"}, {"type": "text", "text": ". It predates modern Python and uses a string-based, functional style."}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}, {"type": "code"}], "text": "pathlib"}, {"type": "text", "text": " was introduced in Python 3.4 and provides an object-oriented way to handle filesystem paths. Instead of manipulating strings and calling standalone functions, you work with "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "Path"}, {"type": "text", "text": " objects that carry both the path and all the operations you'd ever want to do on it. It is the modern, recommended approach for most path-related work."}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Both modules ultimately talk to the same underlying operating system — "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "pathlib"}, {"type": "text", "text": " is largely a cleaner abstraction over what "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "os"}, {"type": "text", "text": " and "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "os.path"}, {"type": "text", "text": " do."}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Why they matter in Generative AI work"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "AI and data pipelines almost always need to:"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Load datasets from directories"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Save model checkpoints and outputs to disk"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Read configuration from environment variables (API keys, model paths, data directories)"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Scan large folder trees recursively for files of a specific type (e.g., all "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": ".txt"}, {"type": "text", "text": " files for a corpus)"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Build reproducible paths that work on macOS, Linux, and Windows"}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Both "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "os"}, {"type": "text", "text": " and "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "pathlib"}, {"type": "text", "text": " are essential for all of this — and using them incorrectly leads to brittle code that only works on the developer's machine."}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "The "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "os"}, {"type": "text", "text": " module"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Environment variables"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "The most common use of "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "os"}, {"type": "text", "text": " in AI/ML work is reading configuration from environment variables — especially API keys, which should never be hardcoded."}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "import os\n\n# Read a variable (returns None if not set)\napi_key = os.environ.get(\"OPENAI_API_KEY\")\n\n# Read with a default fallback\nmodel_name = os.environ.get(\"MODEL_NAME\", \"gpt-4o\")\n\n# Set a variable for the current process\nos.environ[\"MY_VAR\"] = \"hello\"\n\n# Check if a variable exists\nif \"DATABASE_URL\" in os.environ:\n    print(\"DB configured\")"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "os.environ"}, {"type": "text", "text": " behaves like a dictionary. "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "os.environ.get(\"KEY\")"}, {"type": "text", "text": " is always safer than "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "os.environ[\"KEY\"]"}, {"type": "text", "text": " — the dictionary-style access raises a "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "KeyError"}, {"type": "text", "text": " if the variable doesn't exist, while "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": ".get()"}, {"type": "text", "text": " returns "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "None"}, {"type": "text", "text": " or a default."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Current working directory"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "import os\n\n# Where is the script running from?\ncwd = os.getcwd()\nprint(cwd)  # e.g., /home/user/project\n\n# Change directory\nos.chdir(\"/tmp\")"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Creating and removing directories"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "import os\n\n# Create a single directory\nos.mkdir(\"outputs\")\n\n# Create a full nested path in one call (like mkdir -p)\nos.makedirs(\"data/raw/2024\", exist_ok=True)\n\n# Remove an empty directory\nos.rmdir(\"outputs\")\n\n# Remove a file\nos.remove(\"old_file.txt\")\n\n# Rename or move a file\nos.rename(\"old_name.txt\", \"new_name.txt\")"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "The "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "exist_ok=True"}, {"type": "text", "text": " argument on "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "os.makedirs"}, {"type": "text", "text": " is important: without it, the call raises an error if the directory already exists. In scripts that run repeatedly (like training loops), always use "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "exist_ok=True"}, {"type": "text", "text": "."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Listing directory contents"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "import os\n\n# List files and folders in a directory\nentries = os.listdir(\"data\")\nprint(entries)  # ['file1.txt', 'subdir', 'file2.csv']\n\n# Walk an entire directory tree recursively\nfor root, dirs, files in os.walk(\"data\"):\n    for filename in files:\n        full_path = os.path.join(root, filename)\n        print(full_path)"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "os.walk()"}, {"type": "text", "text": " is a generator that yields a tuple of "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "(current_directory, list_of_subdirectories, list_of_files)"}, {"type": "text", "text": " for every directory in the tree. It is the standard way to recursively process all files in a folder."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "os.path"}, {"type": "text", "text": " — the legacy path utility"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Before "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "pathlib"}, {"type": "text", "text": ", all path manipulation went through "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "os.path"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "import os\n\npath = \"/home/user/data/train.csv\"\n\nos.path.basename(path)      # \"train.csv\"\nos.path.dirname(path)       # \"/home/user/data\"\nos.path.splitext(path)      # (\"/home/user/data/train\", \".csv\")\nos.path.join(\"data\", \"raw\", \"file.txt\")  # \"data/raw/file.txt\"\nos.path.exists(path)        # True or False\nos.path.isfile(path)        # True if it's a file\nos.path.isdir(path)         # True if it's a directory\nos.path.abspath(\"file.txt\") # full absolute path"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "os.path.join()"}, {"type": "text", "text": " is critically important for cross-platform compatibility. Hard-coding "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "/"}, {"type": "text", "text": " on macOS/Linux or "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "\\"}, {"type": "text", "text": " on Windows breaks code. "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "os.path.join"}, {"type": "text", "text": " always uses the correct separator for the current OS."}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "The "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "pathlib"}, {"type": "text", "text": " module"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Creating a Path object"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "from pathlib import Path\n\n# Create a path object (does not need to exist yet)\np = Path(\"/home/user/data\")\np = Path(\"relative/path\")\n\n# Current working directory\np = Path.cwd()\n\n# Home directory\np = Path.home()"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "A "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "Path"}, {"type": "text", "text": " object is not a string — it is an object that knows it represents a path. It prints like a string and can be passed to most functions that expect a string path, but it also carries useful methods and properties."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Joining paths with "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "/"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "The single most ergonomic feature of "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "pathlib"}, {"type": "text", "text": " is using the "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "/"}, {"type": "text", "text": " operator to join paths:"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "from pathlib import Path\n\nbase = Path(\"data\")\nfull = base / \"raw\" / \"2024\" / \"train.csv\"\nprint(full)  # data/raw/2024/train.csv"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "This replaces the verbose "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "os.path.join(\"data\", \"raw\", \"2024\", \"train.csv\")"}, {"type": "text", "text": ". The "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "/"}, {"type": "text", "text": " operator automatically uses the correct separator for the operating system."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Path properties"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "from pathlib import Path\n\np = Path(\"/home/user/data/train.csv\")\n\np.name        # \"train.csv\"\np.stem        # \"train\"\np.suffix      # \".csv\"\np.parent      # Path(\"/home/user/data\")\np.parts       # (\"/\", \"home\", \"user\", \"data\", \"train.csv\")"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Checking if paths exist"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "from pathlib import Path\n\np = Path(\"data/train.csv\")\n\np.exists()   # True or False\np.is_file()  # True if it's a regular file\np.is_dir()   # True if it's a directory"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Creating directories"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "from pathlib import Path\n\noutput_dir = Path(\"outputs/checkpoints\")\n\n# Create the full path (like mkdir -p)\noutput_dir.mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "parents=True"}, {"type": "text", "text": " creates all intermediate directories. "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "exist_ok=True"}, {"type": "text", "text": " suppresses the error if the directory already exists. In practice, you will use both together almost every time."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Reading and writing files"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "pathlib"}, {"type": "text", "text": " allows reading and writing file contents directly from the "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "Path"}, {"type": "text", "text": " object — no need to open file handles manually for simple cases:"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "from pathlib import Path\n\np = Path(\"notes.txt\")\n\n# Write text (overwrites if file exists)\np.write_text(\"Hello, world!\\n\", encoding=\"utf-8\")\n\n# Read text\ncontent = p.read_text(encoding=\"utf-8\")\n\n# Write bytes\np.write_bytes(b\"\\x00\\x01\\x02\")\n\n# Read bytes\nraw = p.read_bytes()"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "For larger files or streaming, use "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "p.open()"}, {"type": "text", "text": " which returns a standard file handle:"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "with p.open(\"r\", encoding=\"utf-8\") as f:\n    for line in f:\n        print(line.strip())"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Listing and searching for files"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "from pathlib import Path\n\ndata_dir = Path(\"data\")\n\n# List all immediate children\nfor item in data_dir.iterdir():\n    print(item)\n\n# Find all .txt files in the directory (non-recursive)\nfor txt_file in data_dir.glob(\"*.txt\"):\n    print(txt_file)\n\n# Find all .txt files in all subdirectories (recursive)\nfor txt_file in data_dir.rglob(\"*.txt\"):\n    print(txt_file)"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "rglob(\"*.txt\")"}, {"type": "text", "text": " is the pathlib equivalent of "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "os.walk"}, {"type": "text", "text": " filtered for a pattern — and it is far more readable. The "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "**"}, {"type": "text", "text": " pattern matches any number of subdirectories."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Converting between Path and string"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Most Python libraries accept both strings and "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "Path"}, {"type": "text", "text": " objects. When a library requires a plain string, convert with "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "str()"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "from pathlib import Path\n\np = Path(\"data/train.csv\")\npath_as_string = str(p)       # \"data/train.csv\"\npath_back = Path(path_as_string)"}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Architecture: how they relate"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "The diagram above shows the full picture. Your Python code sits at the top. Both "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "os"}, {"type": "text", "text": " and "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "pathlib"}, {"type": "text", "text": " sit as an interface layer. They both communicate with the operating system's actual filesystem underneath. "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "pathlib"}, {"type": "text", "text": " internally uses many of the same calls that "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "os"}, {"type": "text", "text": " provides — it is built on top of "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "os"}, {"type": "text", "text": ", not a replacement of the OS itself."}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "When to use which"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Use "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}, {"type": "code"}], "text": "pathlib"}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": " for:"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Any path construction, manipulation, or inspection"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Reading and writing small files"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Scanning directories for files matching a pattern"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "New code in Python 3.6+"}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Use "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}, {"type": "code"}], "text": "os"}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": " for:"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Reading environment variables ("}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "os.environ"}, {"type": "text", "text": ")"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Process-level operations (signals, process IDs, "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "os.system"}, {"type": "text", "text": ")"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Renaming or removing files ("}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "os.rename"}, {"type": "text", "text": ", "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "os.remove"}, {"type": "text", "text": ")"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Lower-level OS interactions not covered by pathlib"}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "In practice, most modern Python code uses "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "pathlib"}, {"type": "text", "text": " for paths and "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "os.environ"}, {"type": "text", "text": " for environment variables, and reaches for other "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "os"}, {"type": "text", "text": " functions only when needed."}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Real-world example: loading a dataset directory"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Here is a realistic pattern for an AI data pipeline that needs to find all text files in a data directory, read API configuration from environment variables, and save processed output to a structured folder:"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "import os\nfrom pathlib import Path\n\n# --- Configuration from environment ---\ndata_root = Path(os.environ.get(\"DATA_DIR\", \"data\"))\noutput_root = Path(os.environ.get(\"OUTPUT_DIR\", \"outputs\"))\nmodel_name = os.environ.get(\"MODEL_NAME\", \"default-model\")\n\n# --- Prepare output directory ---\noutput_dir = output_root / model_name / \"processed\"\noutput_dir.mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)\n\n# --- Find all text files recursively ---\ntext_files = list(data_root.rglob(\"*.txt\"))\nprint(f\"Found {len(text_files)} text files\")\n\n# --- Process each file ---\nfor src_file in text_files:\n    content = src_file.read_text(encoding=\"utf-8\")\n    \n    # Preserve relative directory structure in output\n    relative = src_file.relative_to(data_root)\n    dest_file = output_dir / relative\n    dest_file.parent.mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)\n    \n    # Write processed output (example: uppercase)\n    dest_file.write_text(content.upper(), encoding=\"utf-8\")\n    print(f\"Processed: {src_file} -> {dest_file}\")"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "This pattern — environment variable configuration, "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "rglob"}, {"type": "text", "text": " for discovery, "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "relative_to"}, {"type": "text", "text": " for preserving structure, "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)"}, {"type": "text", "text": " before writing — appears constantly in real AI pipelines."}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Common mistakes"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Hard-coding path separators."}, {"type": "text", "text": " Writing "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "\"data/raw/\" + filename"}, {"type": "text", "text": " works on macOS and Linux but breaks on Windows. Always use "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "Path(\"data\") / \"raw\" / filename"}, {"type": "text", "text": " or "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "os.path.join(\"data\", \"raw\", filename)"}, {"type": "text", "text": "."}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Not handling missing directories before writing."}, {"type": "text", "text": " Calling "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "p.write_text(...)"}, {"type": "text", "text": " when the parent directory doesn't exist raises a "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "FileNotFoundError"}, {"type": "text", "text": ". Always call "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "p.parent.mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)"}, {"type": "text", "text": " first."}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Using "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}, {"type": "code"}], "text": "os.environ[\"KEY\"]"}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": " without a try/except or "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}, {"type": "code"}], "text": ".get()"}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "."}, {"type": "text", "text": " This raises "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "KeyError"}, {"type": "text", "text": " if the variable isn't set, crashing the program. Always use "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "os.environ.get(\"KEY\")"}, {"type": "text", "text": " with a fallback, or raise a descriptive error if the variable is required."}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Forgetting "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}, {"type": "code"}], "text": "encoding=\"utf-8\""}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": " on "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}, {"type": "code"}], "text": "read_text"}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": " / "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}, {"type": "code"}], "text": "write_text"}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "."}, {"type": "text", "text": " On Windows, the default encoding is often "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "cp1252"}, {"type": "text", "text": ", which fails on files containing emoji, accented characters, or most non-ASCII text. Always specify "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "encoding=\"utf-8\""}, {"type": "text", "text": "."}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Mixing "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}, {"type": "code"}], "text": "Path"}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": " objects and string concatenation."}, {"type": "text", "text": " "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "str(p) + \"/file.txt\""}, {"type": "text", "text": " is fragile. Use "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "p / \"file.txt\""}, {"type": "text", "text": " instead."}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Treating "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}, {"type": "code"}], "text": "os.listdir"}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": " results as full paths."}, {"type": "text", "text": " "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "os.listdir(\"data\")"}, {"type": "text", "text": " returns "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "[\"file1.txt\", \"subdir\"]"}, {"type": "text", "text": " — just the names, not full paths. Use "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "Path(\"data\").iterdir()"}, {"type": "text", "text": " or prepend the directory manually."}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Best practices"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Always use "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "pathlib"}, {"type": "text", "text": " for new code — it is cleaner, safer, and more readable than "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "os.path"}, {"type": "text", "text": " string manipulation."}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Resolve paths early. If your script takes a directory as an argument, convert it to an absolute resolved path immediately with "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "Path(arg).resolve()"}, {"type": "text", "text": ". This avoids confusion caused by relative paths when the working directory changes."}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "base = Path(\"data\").resolve()"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Use "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "relative_to()"}, {"type": "text", "text": " to preserve directory structure when copying or processing trees. This avoids hard-coded path slicing."}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Store configurable paths as environment variables, not hardcoded strings. This makes the same script work in development, CI, and production without modification."}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "When writing files in loops, check and create parent directories once (before the loop) rather than inside the loop — calling "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "mkdir"}, {"type": "text", "text": " repeatedly on the same path is wasteful even though "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "exist_ok=True"}, {"type": "text", "text": " makes it safe."}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Comparison: "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "os.path"}, {"type": "text", "text": " vs "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "pathlib"}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Task"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "os.path"}, {"type": "text", "text": " style"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "pathlib"}, {"type": "text", "text": " style"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Join paths"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "os.path.join(\"a\", \"b\", \"c\")"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "Path(\"a\") / \"b\" / \"c\""}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Get filename"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "os.path.basename(p)"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "Path(p).name"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Get extension"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "os.path.splitext(p)"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "Path(p).suffix"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Check existence"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "os.path.exists(p)"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "Path(p).exists()"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Read file"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "open(p).read()"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "Path(p).read_text()"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Find files"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "os.walk()"}, {"type": "text", "text": " + filter"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "Path(p).rglob(\"*.txt\")"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Make directory"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "os.makedirs(p, exist_ok=True)"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "Path(p).mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "The "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "pathlib"}, {"type": "text", "text": " style is consistently shorter and more expressive. The only reason to use "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "os.path"}, {"type": "text", "text": " in new code is when targeting Python 2 (now end-of-life) or working with existing code that already uses it."}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Key takeaways"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "os.environ.get(\"KEY\", default)"}, {"type": "text", "text": " is the standard, safe way to read configuration from environment variables — essential for API keys and paths in AI applications."}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "pathlib.Path"}, {"type": "text", "text": " turns filesystem operations into clean method calls on an object, replacing the older "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "os.path"}, {"type": "text", "text": " string-manipulation style."}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "The "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "/"}, {"type": "text", "text": " operator on "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "Path"}, {"type": "text", "text": " objects joins paths correctly on every operating system — prefer it over string concatenation."}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "Path.rglob(\"*.txt\")"}, {"type": "text", "text": " is the cleanest way to find all files matching a pattern across a directory tree."}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Always use "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)"}, {"type": "text", "text": " before writing to a new path, and always specify "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "encoding=\"utf-8\""}, {"type": "text", "text": " when reading or writing text."}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "os"}, {"type": "text", "text": " is still essential for environment variables, process-level operations, and file removal — "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "pathlib"}, {"type": "text", "text": " does not replace all of "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "os"}, {"type": "text", "text": ", only the path-manipulation parts."}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Modern Python AI and data pipelines use "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "pathlib"}, {"type": "text", "text": " for paths and "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "os.environ"}, {"type": "text", "text": " for configuration — together they cover the vast majority of filesystem needs."}]}]}]}]}}